Why I should start on my own:
- I can't get it out of my head and I only have 1 life.
- Having my own game company makes me choose the subject -> Solves advanced level happiness point 1 and all stress points.
- Marlene Mitchell to Zandra Mitchell -> I should never doubt myself. My parents have always supported me, no matter what.
- I somehow feel fortunate to have my fathers genes ->He was able to focus down on a single thing for a long time with sailing to get an understanding.
- Huge personal benefits in creating stuff and becoming better at it -> Ayn Rand Institute speaker 21 convention.
- I am fortunate enough to have the money for it -> See the budget page.
- I can immerse myelf in the work -> Mike Action on c++ programming and the CPU.
- It is something I can do and keep improving at for the rest of my life -> Jonathan Blow, new programming language for games.
- Industry cares about portfolio, not degrees. If I become good at it, I can get jobs everywhere -> Find random job offer.
- I can make my own education in games from the internet and it will be much much better than a "real" education in games -> Handmade Hero Day 1.
- I know how great game mechanics feels like because I have played them on a high level since 1995 -> First game i ever beat was in 1995/1996 and was Super Mario Bros 3 on SNES.
- I can work anywhere on the globe because software is online -> Sandy Goodall lives at two amazing places in the world.
- I get the possibility to work with people who are great at what they do. Whichever field that is. (Architecture article)


What keeps me from starting my own company?
main concerns:
1. My parents would not support me because of the lack in momentary income.
2. My parents would not support me because I would lack education in the real world.
3. My parents would not support me because I will not get any experience working with other people.
4. My parents would not support me because games are not seen as a good productive thing from their perspective.
5. I would have to start the company on funds from my family, which they may find disrespectful.

secondary facts:
6. It takes more than a year to make anything decent in games and probably more than that.
7. I simply do not know how to create or publish a game.
8. I will have trouble organizing my day considering when to work and when not to.
9. I will work "alone" for most of the time.
10. I am not certain the game will provide income in the end.

My answers:
1 = From the budget page I have money doing it for some years if I do not feel guilty about using money I got for free.
2 = I have not agreed with how  the university education system works, and I can learn everything myself, much better, from the internet or my network.
3 = This is true for working in a company, but i get the experience starting my own. And i got the internet and my network.
4 = Games are so new that nobody knows what a game is yet. Braid talks about the atomic bomb. Ask a gamer and a game developer is the dream job.
	-> Jon Blow break room interviews on how he talks to others about his way of living.
5 = This is something I have to ask them about. A small income now vs. a large potential income in some years. Happiness does not come from income, it comes from being good at what you do.
	-> Ayn Rand Institute speaker 21 convention.
6 = That year is not wasted. I get experience, become much more advanced and I have the chance to make my own company.
	-> Jonathan Blow on becoming great at what you do. It is not impossible. Deep work speech.
7 = This I can learn and it is really exciting. I can become great.
	-> Day 1 Handmade Hero.
8 = I can learn from meditation and I know from my work at Ditmer how a "normal" working day feels like.
	-> Doing deep work Jonathan Blow.
9 = This does not scare me at all. I am a person that is good at working alone on my own projects. But i will need to find other developers in the community to talk to. Go to game jams and so on.
	-> Northern GameJam, GOLD or Indiecade.
10 = This is true, but I can always get a "normal" job and earn the money back. I can pull the plug whenever.